procstep.procdesc: A contract was initiated between the SFWMD and the NRCS (Soil Conservation Service)in 1997. Tim Scharff was the contract administrator. NRCS personnel digitized SFWMD canals to match 1mm DOQQs. The lines were attributed PRIMARY, SECONDARY or TERTIARY as well as MAJOR or MINOR. Tim Scharff QA/QC'd the Primary canals, but had Vicky LaBelle working on attributing the secondary and tertiary canals. Vicky left the District sometime in 1998 or 1999 and no one else continued on in her place. However, all the Primary canals were pulled out from this database and became the new "SFWMD Canals" layer.

In May 2009, GeoPlan received this data in shapefile format from the South Florida Water Management District (SFWMD) web portal: http://my.sfwmd.gov/gisapps/sfwmdxwebdc/dataview.asp. The dataset was projected to FGDL Albers HPGN. When received, the data was in State Plane Florida East (FIPS 0901) NAD_1983_HARN Feet.
-Reprojected to FGDL Albers HPGN -Dropped old internal coverage items: fnode_, tnode_, lpoly_, roply_, cover# and cover id -Converted length from feet to meters -Added DESCRIPT field based on NAME to attribute table. Calculated 57 records to "NO DESCRIPT AVAILABLE" -Added FGDLAQDATE based on date data acquired from source -Renamed file from HYSURCRC to SFWMD_CANALS_DEC08
Data imported to ArcSDE and exported as a shapefile.
